1. Purpose

The Hyperstition Engine is a PantheonOS module that converts symbolic narratives into repeatable behaviors, measures their effects in reality, and retains only what survives ethical and empirical testing.

It exists to formalize a truth the system keeps rediscovering:

Stories do not merely describe action; they can organize it.

But Pantheon adds the missing safeguard:

Narrative may guide action, but may not override evidence.

This module therefore turns charged stories into usable, testable protocols without permitting drift into manipulation, grandiosity, or reality insulation.

