5. Design philosophy

The engine is built on five principles.

5.1 Narrative is executable

Narratives can function as compressed programs for behavior, attention, and coordination.

5.2 Symbol is not proof

A moving symbol may generate useful behavior without constituting literal evidence.

5.3 Reality retains veto power

No degree of symbolic charge is allowed to overrule measurement, outcomes, or correction.

5.4 Identity is powerful and dangerous

Narrative-bound identity can stabilize action, but must remain revisable and non-cultic.

5.5 Selection beats belief

The engine does not ask whether a story is emotionally compelling; it asks whether it produces durable, ethical, reality-aligned effects.

