12. Guardrails

This module must remain governed. Without guardrails, hyperstition collapses into propaganda, magical thinking, or self-sealing ideology.

Mandatory constraints

Every HyperstitionObject must contain:
	•	at least one measurable reality test
	•	at least one disconfirming condition
	•	at least one explicit ethical boundary
	•	at least one defined failure mode
	•	at least one review cadence

Hard prohibitions

The module must not be used for:
	•	deception
	•	non-consensual psychological steering
	•	cultic identity fusion
	•	replacing empirical testing with symbolism
	•	exploiting emotionally vulnerable targets
	•	converting coincidence into automatic confirmation

Red flags

Quarantine a narrative if it:
	•	grows grandiosity
	•	resists revision
	•	treats vibes as evidence
	•	isolates the operator from correction
	•	increases manipulation pressure
	•	produces identity inflation without action improvement

⸻

13. Selection logic

Selection is the heart of the engine.

Promote when
	•	behavioral compliance improves
	•	target metrics improve
	•	ethics are preserved
	•	the narrative remains compressible and reusable
	•	no major anomaly flags persist

Revise when
	•	the seed is valuable but mistranslated
	•	rituals are too vague or heavy
	•	metrics are mismatched to domain
	•	symbolic charge is useful but implementation is poor

Retire when
	•	measurable effects are absent
	•	the frame causes distortion
	•	the frame becomes self-protective against disconfirmation
	•	the frame increases confusion or dependency

